<p>Trellis defines several core types that represent CSS layout concepts. These types are used throughout the library to specify sizes, spacing, and constraints.</p>

<h3>Dimension</h3>

<p>The <code>Dimension</code> type represents CSS dimension valuesâ€”how a width or height should be computed:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">inductive Dimension where
  | auto       -- Size from content or context
  | length (n : Float)    -- Explicit pixel value
  | percent (p : Float)   -- Percentage (0.0 to 1.0)
  | minContent -- Minimum content size
  | maxContent -- Maximum content size</code></pre>

