<h3>EdgeInsets</h3>

<p>The <code>EdgeInsets</code> type represents spacing on all four sides, used for margin and padding:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">structure EdgeInsets where
  top : Float
  right : Float
  bottom : Float
  left : Float

-- Constructors
EdgeInsets.uniform 8           -- All sides 8px
EdgeInsets.symmetric 16 8      -- Vertical 16, horizontal 8
EdgeInsets.only (top := 10)    -- Just top, others 0
EdgeInsets.horizontal 20       -- Left and right 20px
EdgeInsets.vertical 10         -- Top and bottom 10px</code></pre>

<h3>BoxConstraints</h3>

<p>The <code>BoxConstraints</code> type combines all sizing and spacing properties for a layout node:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">structure BoxConstraints where
  width : Dimension := .auto
  height : Dimension := .auto
  minWidth : Float := 0
  maxWidth : Option Float := none
  minHeight : Float := 0
  maxHeight : Option Float := none
  margin : EdgeInsets := EdgeInsets.zero
  padding : EdgeInsets := EdgeInsets.zero</code></pre>

<p>Convenience constructors:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">-- Fixed size
BoxConstraints.fixed 200 100

-- Fixed height, auto width
BoxConstraints.fixedHeight 60

-- With min/max constraints
{ BoxConstraints.empty with
  width := .percent 0.5
  minWidth := 100
  maxWidth := some 400
  margin := EdgeInsets.uniform 8
  padding := EdgeInsets.symmetric 16 8
}</code></pre>

<h3>Position</h3>

<p>The <code>Position</code> type controls whether an element participates in normal flow or is positioned absolutely:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">inductive Position where
  | static    -- Normal document flow
  | absolute  -- Positioned relative to containing block</code></pre>

<p>Static positioning (the default) means the element participates in flex or grid layout. Absolute positioning removes the element from the normal flow and positions it relative to its nearest positioned ancestor.</p>

